{
  "_comment": "Ordered payee->category rules. Matched case-insensitively as a substring against 'payee + transaction type'. First match wins. 'category' must EXACTLY match a YNAB category name in the budget. TNG tolls come through as 'RFID Payment'/'PayDirect Payment' types, so we match those types directly. Merchant QR payments come through as type 'Payment' and are matched by name. Unmatched transactions (and all reloads/received inflows) are left uncategorized.",
